> If connection speed even around 3-5mbit, the loading time will be less than 30 seconds.

@slavap note that [Slow 3G seems to introduce a latency of ~2s per request](https://www.debugbear.com/blog/chrome-devtools-network-throttling#what-do-slow-3g-and-fast-3g-mean-in-devtools), so depending on the number of files that are part of their bundle (imagine they also use font assets), those 2 extra seconds can add up quite a bit.

(Not defending OP in this, I'd love to take a look at the app and see where the time is going)

@RodXander That sounds about right. On Slow3G it will be very slow. That said, even with the HTML renderer 45 seconds is already very slow. If supporting Slow3G is important, you might want to use a strategy where your landing page is plain HTML/CSS that loads quickly, and loads Flutter in the background.

Here's a prototype: https://github.com/yjbanov/flutter-landing-demo
Live demo: https://flutter-landing-demo.web.app/

@hmbenhaim I can't tell how the HTML renderer helps here. When you render, say, a button, the HTML renderer will not generate a `<button>` tag but some mishmash of divs and 2D canvases. To Clarity it probably looks like gibberish. I'm surprised that it doesn't work with CanvasKit. Having said that, if Clarity needs to see some HTML under the mouse cursor, consider enabling semantics by doing this:

```dart
void main() {
  runApp(const App());
  if (kIsWeb) {
    SemanticsBinding.instance.ensureSemantics();
  }
}
```

With this Flutter will generate meaningful HTML. We have no plans to remove semantic HTML support in Flutter. Instead, we plan to improve it further.

@zambetpentru https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/129548#issuecomment-2372439809

@mycalls There have been a number of memory-related issues fixed recently, such as:

- https://github.com/flutter/engine/pull/53201
- https://github.com/flutter/engine/pull/54878
- https://github.com/flutter/engine/pull/54818

We will continue working on memory improvements. Specific issues and repros, such as https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/153678, help a lot in fixing this.

@bymoye Although the font issue is listed in the post-deprecation tasks, we'll do our best to fix it before removing the HTML renderer 🤞

@yjbanov 
>> we will continue working hard on reducing payload size

Please please continue reducing payload size, it is still quite big.
